12V to 3V DC–DC Buck Converter Using Arduino PWM Control

This project demonstrates the design and implementation of a DC–DC buck converter for converting a 12 V input supply to a regulated 3 V output. The converter operates on the switching principle, providing efficient voltage reduction compared to linear regulators.

The system consists of an Arduino UNO, MOSFET switching stage, inductor, capacitor filter, diode, and feedback components mounted on a breadboard prototype. The Arduino generates a PWM signal to control the switching operation and regulate the output voltage.

Working Principle
A 12 V DC input is applied to the converter circuit.
The Arduino generates a PWM signal which drives the MOSFET switching element.
During ON time, energy is stored in the inductor.
During OFF time, the stored energy is released through the diode and filter capacitor to the load.
By adjusting the duty cycle, the converter steps down the voltage from 12 V to approximately 3 V DC.
